'''Gebhard of Lahngau''' ({{circa}} 860/868 – 22 June 910), of the [[Conradine]] dynasty, son of [[Udo of Neustria|Odo]] (died 879), count of [[Lahn]]gau, and Judith, was himself count of [[Wetterau]] (909–910) and [[Rheingau]] (897–906) and then [[duke of Lotharingia]] (Lorraine).

In 903, [[Louis the Child]], [[king of Germany]], gave him the government of Lotharingia with the title of duke (''Kebehart dux regni quod a multis Hlotharii dicitur''{{sfn|Stingl|1974|p=101}}).{{sfn|Reuter|2013|p=131}} Gebhard died in battle against the [[Magyars]], somewhere by [[Augsburg]].{{sfn|Reuter|2013|p=131}}

With his wife Ida, he had two children:
*[[Herman I, Duke of Swabia|Herman]] (died 949), [[duke of Swabia]]{{sfn|Reuter|2006|p=696}}
*[[Odo of Wetterau|Odo]] (died 949),{{sfn|Reuter|2006|p=696}} count of Wetterau (from 914), Lahngau (from 918), and Rheingau (from 917), married Cunigunda, daughter of [[Herbert I of Vermandois]]

