{{Spanish name|Alcón|Miquel}} {{Infobox officeholder | name = María José Alcón | image = | office = [[Valencia|City Councilor of Culture of Valencia]] | term_start = 1995 | term_end =2009 |birth_name=María José Alcón Miquel | birth_date = 1961 | birth_place = [[Mislata]], [[Province of Valencia]], Spain | death_date = 16 June 2018 (aged 57) | death_place = [[Callosa d'en Sarrià]], [[Province of Alicante]], Spain |alma_mater= |occupation= Jurist and Politician |spouse=Alfonso Grau (m. 2015 - her death 2018) }} '''María José Alcón i Miquel''' (1961 – 16 June 2018)<ref>[http://www.abc.es/espana/comunidad-valenciana/abci-encuentran-muerta-exconcejal-pp-valencia-maria-jose-alcon-201806161502_noticia.html Encuentran muerta a la exconcejal del PP de Valencia María José Alcón tras precipitarse por un balcón] {{es icon}}</ref> was a Spanish politician from [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]].<ref>[https://ppcv.com/noticias/-el-comite-electoral-de-valencia-ciudad-aprueba-la-propuesta-de-candidatura-municipal-al-ayuntamiento-de-valencia/16036 El Comité Electoral de Valencia Ciudad aprueba la propuesta de candidatura municipal al Ayuntamiento de Valencia] {{es icon}}</ref>
Bachelor of Law and Master's Degree in Urban Law, she held the position of Councilor for Culture<ref>[https://www.valencia.es/ayuntamiento/noticias_accesible.nsf/NoticiasAnterioresWeb/4FCDD355D524F75CC12575230047D724?OpenDocument&lang=1&nivel=2 Mª JOSÉ ALCÓN: “JOAN VERDÚ ES UNO DE LOS PRINCIPALES VALORES DEL ARTE CONTEMPORÁNEO”] {{es icon}}</ref> at the City Council of [[Valencia]] between 1995 and 2009,3 and left office after suffering an accident. After leaving the position of councilor, she continued at City Hall as a consultant, and also continued linked to PP.<ref>[https://elpais.com/ccaa/2012/07/24/valencia/1343158421_773604.html El vicealcalde de Valencia contrata a su pareja] {{es icon}}</ref>
On 2015, she was charged in the ''Taula case'' for [[money laundering]].<ref>[https://www.elperiodico.com/es/politica/20160906/alfonso-grau-imputado-financiacion-ilegal-partido-popular-valencia-5363415 Alfonso Grau, imputado por financiación ilegal del PP de Valencia] {{es icon}}</ref>. In a conversation with his son, recorded by the police, she recognized the alleged money laundering for the financing of the party in Valencia and explained the practice known as ''[[Structuring|smurfing]]'', consisting of some people received cash and at the same time they remitted a transfer for the same amount as a legal donation to the PP<ref>[http://cadenaser.com/emisora/2016/08/16/radio_valencia/1471372805_918197.html Así se repartían las presuntas ‘mordidas’ en el ayuntamiento de Rita Barberá] {{es icon}}</ref>. In this corruption scandal was charged her husband, Alfonso Grau, who was Deputy Mayor between 1995 and 2015, and the former Mayoress [[Rita Barberá]], who died two days after declaring in the [[Supreme Court of Spain|Supreme Court]] in November 2016, both of the same political party. In 2015 she was again charged for a tax crime in the sale of real estate.<ref>[http://www.abc.es/local-comunidad-valenciana/20150618/abci-exedil-maria-jose-alcon-201506181155.html La exedil María José Alcón, imputada por un delito fiscal] {{es icon}}</ref>
Alcón died on 16 June 2018 after falling from the balcony of her house in [[Callosa d'en Sarrià]]. [[Defenestration|Suicide]] is suspected.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/comunidad-valenciana/2018/06/16/5b250078268e3e60788b4663.html Hallan muerta María José Alcón, la ex concejala que confesó por teléfono el blanqueo del PP de Valencia] {{es icon}}</ref>
